parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
despite removing foot from the accelerator
applying brakes
or shifting into neutral or park. The vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied
and the engine may scream or rev loudly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Accelerator pedal becomes stuck in the on position
causing the vehicle to continue accelerating even after the driver releases the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration or deceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cruise control system fails to operate as intended
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to shift gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes squeak
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to respond properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncontrolled acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle fails to respond to throttle input
the vehicle enters "limp mode" without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The suspension failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle falls to the ground
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag sensor can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities. Additionally, faulty sensors can cause incorrect warnings or indicators, leading to driver distraction and potential accidents.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
incorrect passenger seat occupancy detection
inconsistent or intermittent airbag sensor warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can result in serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's safety features are compromised.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
driver or passenger injury due to lack of airbag deployment.
